title: AFC U19 Championship: Oman boys drub Kyrgyzstan
text:
AFC U19 Championship: Oman boys drub Kyrgyzstan October 05, 2015 
Oman routed Kyrgyzstan 4-1 to provisionally take the top spot in Group D of the AFC U19 Championship qualifiers in Doha, Qatar on Sunday. 
Following its goalless draw against Lebanon on Friday, Rasheed Jaber's boys were in dominating form against Kyrgyzstan as they went ahead in the 13th minute through Asad al Awadi. 
Oman pumped in three more goals after the break with Talal al Awadi (54th minute), Zahr al Aghbari (63rd) and Mohsin al Ghassani (75th) finding the target. 
The win took Oman's points tally to four. Defending champion and hosts Qatar were playing their second match against Lebanon in a late game. The hosts won their opening match 7-1 against Kyrgyzstan. 
Oman meets Qatar on Tuesday in its last league match. 
Ten group winners and five best second-placed teams will qualify for the finals, while hosts Bahrain received an automatic qualification. 
If Bahrain finishes atop its qualifying group or as one of the top five second best-placed sides, the next second-placed team will qualify for the final competition. 
UAE triumphs UAE defeated Oman 4-3 in the opening Group C match of the inaugural West Asia U23 Football Championship in Doha, Qatar on Sunday. Hamad al Azzani-coached Oman next takes on Syria in its last group match on Wednesday. Similar content
